data-triple-N3.o: "Malopolska Voivodeship or Malopolska Province, also known as Lesser Poland Voivodeship, is a voivodeship, in southern Poland. It has an area of 15,108 square kilometres, and a population of 3,267,731 (2006). It was created on 1 January 1999 out of the former Krakow, Tarnow, Nowy Sacz and parts of Bielsko-Biala, Katowice, Kielce and Krosno Voivodeships, pursuant to the Polish local government reforms adopted in 1998."@en
